OL,3,CStormont and government urged to end
OL,4,C'penny-pinching betrayal of policing'
OL,6,F"We felt we earned the right to expect
OL,7,Fsomething better from our newly
OL,8,Frestored devolved institutions. That
OL,9,Fwas misplaced confidence on our part.
OL,11,F"Not even having the ability to stand
OL,12,Fstill is a recipe for disaster for the
OL,13,Fservice.
OL,15,F"Right now, we are in the deepest
OL,16,Fresourcing crisis since the formation
OL,17,Fof the PSNI in 2001."
OL,19,FMr Kelly said Stormont ministers must
OL,20,Ftake the fight for a meaningful budget
OL,21,Fto Westminster.
