OL,3,CStormont and government urged to end
OL,4,C'penny-pinching betrayal of policing'
OL,6,F"We are being asked to do the
OL,7,Fimpossible. Regrettably, it's taking a
OL,8,Fheavy toll on our colleagues who are
OL,9,Fworking flat-out in the most trying of
OL,10,Fcircumstances.
OL,12,F"Our paymasters are sleep-walking into
OL,13,Ftrouble."
OL,15,FMr Kelly also raised concerns over a
OL,16,Frise in the number of assaults on
OL,17,Fofficers. He said 3,346 assaults had
OL,18,Fbeen notified in 2022/23.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUuD@IO]
