OL,3,CStormont and government urged to end
OL,4,C'penny-pinching betrayal of policing'
OL,6,F"Incredibly it is probably worse as
OL,7,Fthere is still an element of under-
OL,8,Freporting of assaults by colleagues,"
OL,9,Fhe said.
OL,11,F"The statistics need to reflect the
OL,12,Freality so we can shine a light on the
OL,13,Ftrue extent of this problem."
OL,15,FHe welcomed the commitment by Justice
OL,16,FMinister Ms Long to prioritise new
OL,17,Fsentencing guidelines to deal with
OL,18,Fthose who assault police and emergency
OL,19,Fservice colleagues.
