OL,3,CStormont and government urged to end
OL,4,C'penny-pinching betrayal of policing'
OL,6,F"I hope this isn't an option being
OL,7,Fconsidered in future as it would only
OL,8,Fserve to further devalue the work our
OL,9,Fofficers do daily.
OL,11,F"I fear the repercussions if we become
OL,12,Fthe worst-paid policing service in
OL,13,Fwhat is the most dangerous part of the
OL,14,FUK.
OL,16,F"Our officers, like all others in both
OL,17,Fthe public and private sectors,
OL,18,Fdeserve at the very least to be
OL,19,Ftreated fairly on pay."
